[2] Indonesia
Date: Mon 3 Apr 2006
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: The Jakarta Post, Indonesia, 3 Apr 2006 [edited]
<http://www.thejakartapost.com/detailcity.asp?fileid=20060403.G06&irec=6>

City [greater Jakarta] reports surge in dengue patients
-----------------------------------------------
An official said Sunday [2 Apr 2006] that 7624 dengue fever patients had
been recorded in the past 3 months, with 14 deaths. "During the past 3
months, the number of dengue victims has shown a significant increase,"
said an official at the city health agency, Evy Zelfino. She said there
were 2470 patients in January, 2433 in February and 2718 in March 2006.
Evy urged all residents to keep their environments clean to stop the spread
of the disease. "Apart from keeping our neighborhoods clean, fumigation
should also be carried out regularly," she said. She urged residents to
cover, clean and bury water containers and trash, which are used as
breeding grounds by the [_Aedes aegypti_] mosquitoes that spread dengue.
--
